    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multi-agent debate pits two or more LLM agents against each other in structured rounds of proposal and critique. Each agent reads what the others have said and either refines its position or challenges theirs. A judge synthesizes the final answer from the full debate history. The technique measurably reduces factual errors compared to single-agent generation \u2014 disagreement forces agents to justify their claims."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Multi-agent debate diagram: Debater A and B exchange positions, Judge synthesizes"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to Use Multi-Agent Debate"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "High-stakes factual answers: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "medical, legal, or technical questions where a single LLM may confidently hallucinate."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Design decisions: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "architecture choices, API design, algorithm selection \u2014 where there are real tradeoffs worth surfacing."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Bias reduction: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "assigning agents contrarian roles breaks the model's tendency to agree with any prior framing."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Avoid: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "simple retrieval tasks (debate overhead is pure cost), very long documents (each agent sees the full history each round \u2014 context grows fast), or tasks with a single clear correct answer discoverable by tool use."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
